commentPostTextItems.html: How many times have we seen Hussey do a Bevan now? His superb innings seals Australia's spot in the final. Credit to New Zealand for fighting as hard as they did. McMillan set the match up with a belligerent 89 but New Zealand could have done with a few more runs. Australia's chase started poorly - they lost their first three wickets for 17 but Clarke and Hussey played gritty innings to seal Australia's victory.

Thank you for tuning into Cricinfo's live coverage of today's game. We'll be back on Tuesday when England take on New Zealand at Adelaide. That will be a crucial match for New Zealand who haven't picked up any points so far. Do join us then. Cheers!
